### Step 1: Get all roles and find "superior" role
GET http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/roles
Content-Type: application/json

###

### Step 2: Get all permissions (to get their IDs)
GET http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/permissions
Content-Type: application/json

###

### Step 3: Attach all permissions to "superior" role
# Replace {SUPERIOR_ROLE_ID} with the actual UUID from Step 1
# Replace the permissionIds array with all permission IDs from Step 2
PATCH http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/roles/{SUPERIOR_ROLE_ID}/permissions/add
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "permissionIds": [
    "permission-uuid-1",
    "permission-uuid-2",
    "permission-uuid-3",
    "permission-uuid-4",
    "permission-uuid-5",
    "permission-uuid-6",
    "permission-uuid-7",
    "permission-uuid-8",
    "permission-uuid-9",
    "permission-uuid-10"
  ]
}

###

### Alternative: Get specific role by name (if search/filter is available)
# Use this to directly get the superior role
GET http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/roles?name=superior
Content-Type: application/json

###

### Verify: Get the superior role with its permissions
GET http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/roles/{SUPERIOR_ROLE_ID}
Content-Type: application/json
